dc_title_s: Railroad Stations, San Mateo County Sea Level Rise Vulnerability Assessment Project Area, 2015
dc_description_s: This point shapefile represents CalTrain stations in San Mateo County. Caltrain has 32 stations from San Francisco to Gilroy. Passengers wait for and board trains at these stations. Source: San Mateo County Transit District (2015). Acquired: August 2015. This layer is part of the San Mateo County Sea Level Rise Vulnerability Assessment Project. These data are intended for researchers, students, and policy makers for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production.

dc_creator_sm: County of San Mateo Information Services Department
